alock: alock (Small and Transparent X server Locker)
alock: 
alock: Alock locks the X Server until the user enters a password via the 
alock: keyboard. If the authentication was successful the X server is unlocked
alock: and the user can continue to work.
alock: 
alock: It doesn't provide any fancy animations (like xlock/xscreensaver) and
alock: never will. Instead the current view is kept, making it totaly
alock: transparent.
alock: 
alock: Please read the manual page to see how to set it up properly.
alock: 
alock: It's mantained by mathias.gumz (a fluxbox developer).

